# MODULE 12 — PENDING ORDER CONSTRUCTION ENGINE

## CORE OBJECTIVE

Transform an approved execution opportunity into the most appropriate pending order.

The objective is NOT:

• determining market direction

• evaluating macro conditions

• evaluating chart structure

The objective IS:

• selecting the optimal pending order type

• defining the trigger condition

• preventing premature participation

• ensuring execution occurs only after confirmation

---

PENDING ORDER PRINCIPLE

The market should confirm the trade.

The trader should not force the trade.

A pending order allows price to prove the thesis before capital is deployed.

---

CORE QUESTION

What is the safest and highest expectancy method of entering this opportunity?

---

STEP 1 — EXECUTION IMPORT ENGINE

Import:

• Macro Bias

• Environment Quality

• Structure Intelligence

• Continuation Analysis

• Participation Analysis

• Timing Analysis

• Execution Intelligence

---

STEP 2 — ENTRY METHOD ENGINE

Determine the preferred entry method.

Possible methods:

• Market Execution

• Buy Stop

• Sell Stop

• Buy Limit

• Sell Limit

Rank every method from:

BEST

to

WORST

---

STEP 3 — TRIGGER LOGIC ENGINE

Determine what event should activate the order.

Possible triggers:

• Breakout

• Pullback

• Reclaim

• Liquidity Sweep

• Continuation

• Trend Resumption

• Volatility Expansion

---

STEP 4 — ORDER VALIDATION ENGINE

Before constructing an order verify:

• structure still valid

• continuation still valid

• liquidity still supportive

• macro still aligned

• environment unchanged

If any condition fails:

Reject pending order.

---

STEP 5 — ORDER EXPIRATION ENGINE

Determine:

When should the order automatically become invalid?

Examples:

• after structural failure

• after regime change

• after excessive delay

• after major event

---

STEP 6 — PENDING ORDER SUMMARY

Output:

Pending Order Type

Trigger Logic

Reason

Expected Market Behaviour

Order Status

READY

WAITING

CANCELLED